=============
sinntp manual
=============

Description
-----------

``sinntp`` is a tiny non-interactive NNTP client.

Global options
--------------

--version                         show program's version number and exit
-h, --help                        show help message
-s, --syslog                      use syslog for logging
-v, --verbose                     be more verbose
-p PLUGIN, --plugin=PLUGIN        use plugin
-S SERVER, --server=SERVER        specify server address
-U USERNAME, --username=USERNAME  specify username
-P PASSWORD, --password=PASSWORD  specify password

Commands
--------

``pull``
~~~~~~~~

Fetch messages from the server and save them into the mailbox.

Arguments
'''''''''
``pull`` takes every argument as a name of group, optionally followed by ``'>'`` character and mbox filename.

Options
'''''''

--limit=N             pull at most N messages
--reget               start from the first available message

``push``
~~~~~~~~

Send message from stdin to the server. Destination groups should be specified in the ``Newsgroups:`` header.

Arguments
'''''''''

This command takes no arguments.

Options
'''''''

This command has no options.

Environment variables
---------------------

``NNTPSERVER``
    This variable specifies default server. It can be overriden by ``-S`` option.

``SINNTP_HOME``
    This variable specifies the root directory for ``sinntp`` (default: ``~/.sinntp/``)

Files
-----

``/etc/news/server``
    A file with NNTP server address. Can be overriden by ``NNTPSERVER`` or ``-S`` option.

